ll,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Symptom\n\nDashboard CI on current main fails in `pnpm test` after merge commit `437262e5d91e66810f6f8b106f9760772a3217e9` / PR #12162.\n\nObserved run: https://github.com/jeong-sik/masc-mcp/actions/runs/25146869513\n\nThe Dashboard job fails with broad Preact hook-state exceptions across unrelated existing tests, for example:\n\n- `TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading '__H')`\n- `TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading '__$f')`\n\nThe same inherited failure appears on draft PR #12165 Dashboard job even though that PR touches no dashboard files.\n\n## Reproduction condition\n\nRun dashboard CI or locally run from `dashboard/` on main after #12162:\n\n```bash\npnpm test\n```\n\nCI uses:\n\n```bash\nvitest run --no-file-parallelism --maxWorkers=1\n```\n\n## Suspected cause\n\nPR #12162 added SolidJS PoC dependencies and Vite/Vitest Solid plugin config. The failure shape suggests Solid/Preact test transforms or runtime setup are leaking into existing Preact test modules, breaking Preact hook state during renders.\n\nChanged files from #12162 include:\n\n- `dashboard/vite.config.ts`\n- `dashboard/vitest.config.ts`\n- `dashboard/package.json`\n- `dashboard/pnpm-lock.yaml`\n- `dashboard/design-system/headless-solid/*`\n- `dashboard/design-system/preview/solid-*`\n\n## Tried / evidence\n\n- Confirmed #12165 diff has no dashboard files.\n- Confirmed current main CI run `25146869513` fails in Dashboard before #12165-specific OCaml jobs matter.\n- Confirmed #12165 PR run `25147195772` fails in Dashboard with the same Preact hook-state error family.\n\n[근거] GitHub Actions run links above, checked 2026-04-30 Asia/Seoul, confidence High.\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/jeong-sik/masc-mcp/issues/12185/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/jeong-sik/masc-mcp/issues/12185/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ryansolid/dom-expressions/issues/500","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ryansolid/dom-expressions","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ryansolid/dom-expressions/issues/500/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ryansolid/dom-expressions/issues/500/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ryansolid/dom-expressions/issues/500/events","html_url":"https://github.com/ryansolid/dom-expressions/issues/500","id":4248282058,"node_id":"I_kwDOCrk3d879N6PK","number":500,"title":"[SSR] Two regressions in v0.41.0-next.17: `results is not defined` and `JSXEmptyExpression` error","user":{"login":"ljho01","id":81096766,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjgxMDk2NzY2","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/81096766?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/ljho01","html_url":"https://github.com/ljho01","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ljho01/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ljho01/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ljho01/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ljho01/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ljho01/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ljho01/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ljho01/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ljho01/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/ljho01/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":2,"created_at":"2026-04-12T14:00:37Z","updated_at":"2026-04-14T20:44:48Z","closed_at":"2026-04-14T20:44:48Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Bug 1: `results is not defined` in SSR `createElement` when element has both `ref` and spread\n\n**Version:** babel-plugin-jsx-dom-expressions@0.41.0-next.17 (via babel-preset-solid@2.0.0-experimental.16, solid-js@2.0.0-beta.6)\n\n**Reproduction:**\n```tsx\nfunction MyComponent(props) {\n  let el\n  const [local, others] = splitProps(props, ['children'])\n  return <div ref={el} {...others}>{local.children}</div>\n}\n```\n\nBuild with `generate: \"ssr\"` → throws `ReferenceError: results is not defined`\n\nClient build (`generate: \"dom\"`) works fine.\n\n**Root cause:**\nIn `createElement` function (index.js:2917), the `ref` attribute handler at line ~2976-2979 references `results.declarations.push(...)`, but `results` is never declared in the `createElement` function scope. \n\nIn v0.40.6, the same `ref` case simply did `return;` without referencing `results`. This appears to be a regression where code was copied from `transformElement$2` (where `results` IS in scope) into `createElement` (where it is not).\n\n## Bug 2: `JSXEmptyExpression` error with bare boolean `muted` attribute on `<video>`\n\n**Version:** Same as above.\n\n**Reproduction:**\n```tsx\nfunction MyVideo() {\n  return <video src=\"test.mp4\" muted />\n}\n```\n\nBuild with SSR → throws:\n```\nTypeError: Property right of AssignmentExpression expected node to be of a type [\"Expression\"] but instead got \"JSXEmptyExpression\"\n```\n\n**Root cause:**\n`muted` is listed as a stateful DOM property in the plugin's special handling (index.js:27, `VIDEO: { muted: 1 }`). When a bare boolean attribute (`muted` without `={true}`) hits this code path, the value is `JSXEmptyExpression` which cannot be used as an assignment right-hand side.\n\n**Workaround:** Use explicit `muted={true}` instead of bare `muted`.\n\n## Environment\n- solid-js: 2.0.0-beta.6\n- babel-preset-solid: 2.0.0-experimental.16\n- babel-plugin-jsx-dom-expressions: 0.41.0-next.17\n- vite: 8.0.7\n- Node: 24\n\nBoth bugs only manifest in SSR builds, not client builds.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ryansolid/dom-expressions/issues/500/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/ryansolid/dom-expressions/issues/500/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Quackster/HabboWidgets/issues/16","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Quackster/HabboWidgets","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Quackster/HabboWidgets/issues/16/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Quackster/HabboWidgets/issues/16/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Quackster/HabboWidgets/issues/16/events","html_url":"https://github.com/Quackster/HabboWidgets/issues/16","id":3998152800,"node_id":"I_kwDORQydCM7uTvhg","number":16,"title":"Feature Request: Restore original AS3, create transpiler","user":{"login":"emansom","id":981494,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk4MTQ5NA==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/981494?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/emansom","html_url":"https://github.com/emansom","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/emansom/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/emansom/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/emansom/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/emansom/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/emansom/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/emansom/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/emansom/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/emansom/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/emansom/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":4,"created_at":"2026-02-26T22:51:58Z","updated_at":"2026-05-10T14:03:52Z","closed_at":"2026-05-10T14:03:52Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"## Description\n\nCurrently we have little to no control over how \"AI\" is transforming from assets and snippets AS3 to a functional recreation. It works, but it is not reliable and verifiable as it relies on external black box infrastructure.\n\nBeing reliant on \"AI\" services to ad infinitum, that could change their usefulness and behavior at any moment, seems not a very smart move from a maintainability perspective.\n\n## Proposed solution\n\nCreate a transpiler that takes in the .swf, parses its AS3 and spits out a modern Vite project that utilizes [EaselJS](https://github.com/CreateJS/EaselJS)\n\nEaselJS seems like a perfect fit as it was designed with AS3 API compatibility in mind. Bonuspoint for some way to bring it up to modern tech. Some bindings to SolidJS similar to [solid-canvas](https://github.com/bigmistqke/solid-canvas) would be nice. Having some declarative way of programming the whole UI would be stellar.\n\n## Prior art\n\nhttps://github.com/innogames/ax3\nhttps://github.com/geekrelief/as3tohaxe\nhttps://github.com/ruffle-rs/ruffle\nhttps://github.com/ArachisH/Flazzy\n\n## Useful links\nhttps://github.com/CreateJS/EaselJS\nhttps://github.com/loilo-inc/easeljs-react\nhttps://github.com/bigmistqke/solid-canvas\nhttps://webdesign.tutsplus.com/getting-started-with-easeljs-a-flash-like-interface-for-the-html5-canvas--active-10382a\nhttps://stackoverflow.com/questions/32215678/easeljs-as3-to-javascript-conversion-on-rollover-of-mc-gotoandplay-frame-1-of\nhttps://github.com/konvajs/konva\nhttps://github.com/konvajs/react-konva","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Quackster/HabboWidgets/issues/16/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/Quackster/HabboWidgets/issues/16/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"not_planned","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/TanStack/router/issues/7240","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/TanStack/router","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/TanStack/router/issues/7240/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/TanStack/router/issues/7240/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/TanStack/router/issues/7240/events","html_url":"https://github.com/TanStack/router/issues/7240","id":4310298432,"node_id":"I_kwDOCd_tpc8AAAABAOnvQA","number":7240,"title":"[solid-router] FOUC on client-side navigation — stylesheet <link> sometimes remounted between routes","user":{"login":"jakst","id":3687893,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM2ODc4OTM=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3687893?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/jakst","html_url":"https://github.com/jakst","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jakst/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jakst/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jakst/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jakst/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jakst/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jakst/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jakst/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jakst/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/jakst/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":8180967704,"node_id":"LA_kwDOCd_tpc8AAAAB55-pGA","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/TanStack/router/labels/package:%20solid-router","name":"package: solid-router","color":"FEF7ED","default":false,"description":""}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-04-22T16:06:45Z","updated_at":"2026-04-25T16:25:43Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T16:25:43Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Which project does this relate to?\n\nRouter (`@tanstack/solid-router` + `@tanstack/router-core`)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nWe noticed an occasional Flash of Unstyled Content when navigating between pages on our production build. The app would render briefly with no styles, then snap back to the correct look. It wasn't random, some route transitions always triggered it, others never did. It never happens in `vite dev`, only in a built app.\n\nLooking in DevTools → Network with \"Disable cache\" on, we saw the app's CSS file being re-requested on exactly the navigations that flashed. The `<link rel=\"stylesheet\">` element in `<head>` was being removed and a new one with the same `href` inserted right after, and during the gap it painted an unstyled frame.\n\n### Your Example Website or App\n\nhttps://github.com/jakst/tss-css-reloads\n\n### Steps to Reproduce the Bug or Issue\n\n1. `git clone https://github.com/jakst/tss-css-reloads && pnpm install`\n2. `pnpm build && pnpm preview`\n3. Open the preview URL.\n4. DevTools → Network → check **Disable cache**, filter to **CSS**.\n5. Click around between **Home / A / B / C** in the nav.\n6. Notice that the CSS file is re-requested on some transitions (e.g. `A → B`, `B → A`) and a FOUC is visible on those.\n7. Optional: right-click the CSS request and throttle its URL to Slow 3G for a longer flash.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nClient-side navigation should leave an unchanged `<link rel=\"stylesheet\">` alone. The browser should not be re-fetching the CSS on every nav.\n\n### Platform\n\n- `@tanstack/solid-router@1.168.20`\n- `@tanstack/router-core@1.168.15`\n- `@tanstack/solid-start@1.167.37`\n- `@solidjs/meta@0.29.4`\n- `solid-js@1.9.12`\n- Vite 7.3.2\n- macOS, Chromium-family browsers (also reproduces in Safari)\n\n---\n\n### Debugging notes (LLM-assisted — treat as a hypothesis, not confirmed)\n\n> I debugged this together with an LLM. The section below is its best-effort read of the code; I haven't independently verified every claim. Posting it in case it's a useful starting point.\n\nThe common factor across the transitions that flash is that one route's match chain contributes a different number of `modulepreload` links than the other's. `/b` being a parent+child adds an extra preload; `/a` and `/c` have the same preload count, which is why `A ↔ C` doesn't flash.\n\nThe LLM pointed at `packages/solid-router/src/headContentUtils.tsx`, where `useTags` flattens all head tags into a single positional array and diffs with `replaceEqualDeep`:\n\n```ts\nreturn Solid.createMemo((prev) => {\n\tconst next = uniqBy(\n\t\t[\n\t\t\t...meta(),\n\t\t\t...preloadLinks(), // length varies per match chain\n\t\t\t...links(), // contains <link rel=\"stylesheet\"> from root head()\n\t\t\t...styles(),\n\t\t\t...headScripts(),\n\t\t],\n\t\t(d) => JSON.stringify(d)\n\t)\n\tif (prev === undefined) return next\n\treturn replaceEqualDeep(prev, next)\n})\n```\n\n`replaceEqualDeep` compares positionally. When `preloadLinks().length` differs between prev and next, every tag after the preloads shifts index, so the stylesheet tag object gets a new identity even though an identical tag exists elsewhere in `prev`.\n\n`HeadContent` renders these tags via Solid's `<For>`, which is keyed by strict object identity. When the stylesheet tag loses its identity, `<For>` disposes the old `<Asset>` / `<Link>`. `@solidjs/meta`'s `<Link>` runs `onCleanup`, which physically removes the `<link rel=\"stylesheet\">` element from the DOM. The replacement `<Link>` then creates and appends a new one — which is what we see in the Network tab as a fresh CSS request.\n\nSuggested direction (again, LLM hypothesis): replace the positional `replaceEqualDeep` with an unordered, key-based identity map so any tag whose serialized form appears in `prev` keeps its identity regardless of position. Something roughly like:\n\n```ts\nreturn Solid.createMemo((prev) => {\n  const nextArr = uniqBy([...], (d) => JSON.stringify(d))\n  if (!prev) return nextArr\n\n  const prevByKey = new Map<string, RouterManagedTag>()\n  for (const t of prev) prevByKey.set(JSON.stringify(t), t)\n\n  let changed = nextArr.length !== prev.length\n  const result = nextArr.map((t, i) => {\n    const key = JSON.stringify(t)\n    const existing = prevByKey.get(key)\n    if (existing) {\n      if (existing !== prev[i]) changed = true\n      return existing // preserve identity regardless of position\n    }\n    changed = true\n    return t\n  })\n\n  return changed ? result : prev\n})\n```\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/TanStack/router/issues/7240/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":1},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/TanStack/router/issues/7240/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid/issues/2611","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid/issues/2611/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid/issues/2611/comments","events_url":"https