pe: `get: Store<T> & { [$REFRESH]: any }`.\n\nHowever, `solid-js` defines it simply as `Store<T>`:\n\nhttps://github.com/solidjs/solid/blob/22fb14650f794b78d5020832d70c8323451f7b56/packages/solid/src/client/hydration.ts#L689-L696\n\nEither the intention was to include `[$REFRESH]` explicitly again in the re-export and this is just a typo (the [actions spec](https://github.com/solidjs/solid/blob/next/documentation/solid-2.0/06-actions-optimistic.md#refresh-explicit-recomputation) suggests that it was), or add it to the `Store` type itself. The latter seems somewhat less likely, since only the derived form `createStore(() => ...)` would be “refreshable”.\n\n### Your Example Website or App\n\nhttps://github.com/solidjs/solid/blob/next/documentation/solid-2.0/06-actions-optimistic.md#createoptimisticstore-optimistic-store\n\n### Steps to Reproduce the Bug or Issue\n\nThe example taken directly from the RFC doesn't compile with TypeScript enabled when importing `createOptimisticStore` from `solid-js` rather than directly from `@solidjs/signals`\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n...\n\n### Screenshots or Videos\n\n_No response_\n\n### Platform\n\nAny\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid/issues/2611/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid/issues/2611/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs-community/solid-three/issues/40","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs-community/solid-three","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs-community/solid-three/issues/40/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs-community/solid-three/issues/40/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs-community/solid-three/issues/40/events","ht