","assignee":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Describe the bug\n\nA `<For>` loop's `props` become `undefined` when a different has a textContent interpolation site.\n\n### Your Example Website or App\n\nhttps://playground.solidjs.com/anonymous/b2f0f6af-64e6-4076-9778-c474624a1e3e\n\n### Steps to Reproduce the Bug or Issue\n\n1. see the playground link\n2. notice it has an error `Uncaught TypeError: Cannot use 'in' operator to search for 'fallback' in undefined` because `props` passed into the `For` component is `undefined`\n3. remove the `<style>` tag and the error goes away.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe `For` shouldn't be broken.\n\n### Screenshots or Videos\n\n<img width=\"853\" height=\"143\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a3f826dc-d7d6-4cf9-8980-5321e566673e\" />\n\n### Platform\n\n- OS: macOS\n- Browser: Chrome/Safari\n- Version: 144/26\n\n\n### Additional context\n\nLooks like this is specific to `html`. I can't reproduce with JSX:\n\nhttps://playground.solidjs.com/anonymous/813a4dc5-31b8-4bbc-9acc-036da13224d4","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid/issues/2582/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid/issues/2582/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/kobaltedev/kobalte/issues/651","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/kobaltedev/kobalte","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/kobaltedev/kobalte/issues/651/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/kobaltedev/kobalte/issues/651/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/kobaltedev/kobalte/issues/651/events","html_url":"https://github.com/kobaltedev/kobalte/issues/651","id":4402989111,"node_id":"I_kwDOIU3PE88AAAABBnBINw","number":651,"title":"DropdownMenu content portal silently fails to mount when Content body re-evaluates under fast updates","user":{"login":"LorenzoWynberg","id":7880769,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjc4ODA3Njk=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7880769?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/LorenzoWynberg","html_url":"https://github.com/LorenzoWynberg","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LorenzoWynberg/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LorenzoWynberg/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LorenzoWynberg/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LorenzoWynberg/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LorenzoWynberg/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LorenzoWynberg/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LorenzoWynberg/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LorenzoWynberg/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/LorenzoWynberg/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":3,"created_at":"2026-05-08T01:05:10Z","updated_at":"2026-05-08T02:12:08Z","closed_at":"2026-05-08T02:12:08Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"# `DropdownMenu` content portal silently fails to mount when `Content` body re-evaluates under fast updates\n\n## Summary\n\nWhen a controlled `DropdownMenu`'s `Content` body contains reactive `<Show>` / `<For>` / signal reads that re-evaluate from a frequently-firing source (e.g. a `setInterval` mutating signals every 1.5 s), clicking the trigger correctly flips its `data-expanded` to `\"\"` and `aria-expanded` to `\"true\"`, but the `Portal` > `Content` is never inserted into the DOM. The state machine reports \"open\"; the user sees nothing.\n\n**The failure is sticky.** Once the mount fails, the menu is wedged for the lifetime of the component instance: stopping the interval and clicking again leaves the trigger at `aria-expanded=\"false\"` / no `data-expanded` (the click is ignored), and content still doesn't appear. Only remounting / reloading the page recovers.\n\nIf the `Content` body is static (only `<DropdownMenu.Item>`s, no signal reads), the bug does not appear under the same conditions.\n\n## Versions\n\n- `@kobalte/core` 0.13.11 (also reproduces on 0.13.10 in the original codebase)\n- `solid-js` 1.9.x\n- Verified in **both** Chromium and WebKit via Playwright — not engine-specific.\n\n## Repro\n\nRepository: https://github.com/LorenzoWynberg/kobalte-dropdownmenu-portal-repro\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/LorenzoWynberg/kobalte-dropdownmenu-portal-repro\ncd kobalte-dropdownmenu-portal-repro\npnpm install\npnpm dev\n# open http://localhost:5173\n```\n\nSteps:\n\n1. Click **Open dropdown** (bottom-left). Panel appears. Close it. ✅\n2. Click **Start fast-poll** — `count` rises every 1.5 s.\n3. Wait ~3 s, click **Open dropdown** again. Panel does **not** appear. ❌\n   - Diagnostics box shows: `aria-expanded = \"true\"`, `data-expanded = \"\"`, **`content nodes in DOM = 0`**.\n4. Click **Stop fast-poll**. Click the trigger again. Still does not open — `aria-expanded` now stays `\"false\"`, the click is silently ignored. ❌\n5. Reload the page, click **Open dropdown**. Panel appears. ✅\n\nSo the failure is not transient — it persists after the trigger condition is removed.\n\nTo verify the role of reactive content, append `?staticContent=1` and repeat step 3 — the panel appears even with poll on.\n\n## Automated repro\n\n`node verify.mjs` (Playwright, runs against the dev server). Output on a successful repro:\n\n```\n=== Phase 1: poll OFF, click trigger ===\n{ triggerDataExpanded: '', triggerAriaExpanded: 'true', contentNodes: 1 }    ← works\n\n=== Phase 2: poll ON for 4 s, then click trigger ===\n{ triggerDataExpanded: '', triggerAriaExpanded: 'true', contentNodes: 0 }    ← bug fires\n\n=== Phase 3: SAME page, poll OFF, click trigger (stickiness check) ===\n{ triggerDataExpanded: null, triggerAriaExpanded: 'false', contentNodes: 0 }  ← still broken\n\n=== Phase 4: fresh page, poll OFF, click trigger (recovery check) ===\n{ triggerDataExpanded: '', triggerAriaExpanded: 'true', contentNodes: 1 }    ← recovers on reload\n\n=== Verdict ===\n{ baselineWorks: true, bugFires: true, bugStickyAfterPollStops: true, recoversOnReload: true }\nBUG REPRODUCED ✅ — sticky variant: stays broken after poll stops, recovers only on reload.\n```\n\n`ENGINE=webkit node verify.mjs` reproduces identically.\n\n## Minimal code\n\n[`src/App.tsx`](./src/App.tsx) — ~140 lines, two signals (`count`, `pulse`) mutated on a 1.5 s interval, one `<DropdownMenu>` (controlled, `placement=\"top-start\"`, `modal={false}`, `gutter={4}`). Content body has a `<Show when={count() > 0}>` and a `<For each={...}>` that read those signals.\n\n## Expected\n\nClicking the trigger when `open=false` results in `open=true` AND `Portal > Content` mounted, regardless of how often the `Content` body's reactive scope re-evaluates.\n\n## Observed\n\n`open` propagates to the trigger (`data-expanded`, `aria-expanded`). The `Portal > Content` mount is silently skipped — `document.querySelectorAll('[data-testid=\"content\"]').length === 0` 250 ms after the click. A `MutationObserver` on `document.body { childList: true }` shows zero additions during the failing click.\n\n## Likely area\n\nThe `Content`'s mount lifecycle (presence-state / animation-presence / lazy-portal) appears to drift apart from the trigger's open state under reactive churn in the same content body. After the first failed mount, the menu's internal state appears wedged — subsequent click events flip `open` back to `false` immediately rather than opening, suggesting the open-state machine and the mount lifecycle have desynced and can't recover within the component's lifetime.\n\nA plain Solid `<Show when={open()}><Portal>…</Portal></Show>` over the same `open` signal mounts content reliably under identical churn — that's the workaround we shipped.\n\n## Workaround\n\nSet `forceMount` on the `DropdownMenu` root:\n\n```tsx\n<DropdownMenu open={open()} onOpenChange={setOpen} forceMount>\n```\n\nWith `forceMount`, all three phases pass in this repro. Per `MenuRootOptions`'s own docstring, `forceMount` is \"useful when controlling animation with SolidJS animation libraries\" — but it's also the only way we've found to get reliable mounting for non-animated content whose body re-evaluates frequently.\n\nA heavier hand-rolled alternative — replacing `<DropdownMenu>` entirely with `<Show when={open()}><Portal>…</Portal></Show>` — also works.\n\n## Notes\n\n- `modal={false}` is what we use; haven't yet checked whether `modal={true}` is required for the bug.\n- HMR is **not** required to repro — fresh page load + fast-poll on + click reproduces (verified via Playwright fresh contexts).\n- Synthetic `dispatchEvent(new PointerEvent(...))` and real Playwright clicks both reproduce — not gated on `isTrusted`.\n- Verified in our app (Trinity, a SolidJS Tauri desktop app) against the same Kobalte version.\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/kobaltedev/kobalte/issues/651/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/kobaltedev/kobalte/issues/651/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https: