":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid/issues/2107","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid/issues/2107/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid/issues/2107/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid/issues/2107/events","html_url":"https://github.com/solidjs/solid/issues/2107","id":2201368927,"node_id":"I_kwDOB80jds6DNjlf","number":2107,"title":"Batch top level effects to make them behave consistent with regular effects","user":{"login":"titoBouzout","id":64156,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY0MTU2","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/64156?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/titoBouzout","html_url":"https://github.com/titoBouzout","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/titoBouzout/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/titoBouzout/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/titoBouzout/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/titoBouzout/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/titoBouzout/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/titoBouzout/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/titoBouzout/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/titoBouzout/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/titoBouzout/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":912631390,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWw5MTI2MzEzOTA=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid/labels/enhancement","name":"enhancement","color":"a2eeef","default":true,"description":"New feature or request"}],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":2,"created_at":"2024-03-21T23:15:49Z","updated_at":"2026-04-23T00:21:53Z","closed_at":"2026-04-23T00:21:53Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Describe the bug\n\nTop level effects (`createEffect` that isn't wrapped in a `createRoot`)  behave inconsistently when compared with effects under a root, because top level effects aren't batched. \r\n\r\nThis isn't an issue with solid per se, as its `render` function already wraps in a `root`. \r\n\r\nThe issue is when solid is used for reactivity exclusively(besides rendering dom nodes), such when creating long-lived effects that will never be disposed, reactivity in the server; or for demo purposes (such playground snippets and the like), this inconsistency gets in the way because doesn't match expectations, it could be hard to understand why does behave this way. \r\n\r\nIt is possible that batching top level effects improve the performance of these effects.\n\n### Your Example Website or App\n\nmeaw\n\n### Steps to Reproduce the Bug or Issue\n\nTop level effect non batched\r\nhttps://playground.solidjs.com/anonymous/39d404d1-5c4a-411b-ab85-f915c82089e6\r\n\r\nbehaves differently to:\r\n\r\neffect wrapped in a root\r\nhttps://playground.solidjs.com/anonymous/d30de401-fc16-4c9a-a247-39333b970b8b\r\nbehaves the same as a top level effect that uses batch\r\nhttps://playground.solidjs.com/anonymous/13b29236-c0f9-46fb-8b20-4a221fa9e4df\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nPlease batch top level effects.\n\n### Screenshots or Videos\n\n_No response_\n\n### Platform\n\n- OS: [e.g. macOS, Windows, Linux]\r\n- Browser: [e.g. Chrome, Safari, Firefox]\r\n- Version: [e.g. 91.1]\r\n\n\n### Additional context\n\nAs discussed on discord, it may be about changing this line https://github.com/solidjs/solid/blob/main/packages/solid/src/reactive/signal.ts#L357","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid/issues/2107/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid/issues/2107/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid-start/issues/2108","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid-start","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid-start/issues/2108/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid-start/issues/2108/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid-start/issues/2108/events","html_url":"https://github.com/solidjs/solid-start/issues/2108","id":4079422724,"node_id":"I_kwDOFQg8ps7zJw0E","number":2108,"title":"[Bug?]: `2.0.0-alpha.2` hydration mismatch on initial scroll with Kobalte `CollapsibleTrigger` and `lucide-solid` `ChevronDown`","user":{"login":"pRizz","id":3519085,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM1MTkwODU=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3519085?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/pRizz","html_url":"https://github.com/pRizz","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pRizz/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pRizz/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pRizz/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pRizz/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pRizz/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pRizz/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pRizz/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pRizz/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/pRizz/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"labels":[],"state":"closed","locked":false,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2026-03-15T23:14:57Z","updated_at":"2026-03-16T01:06:09Z","closed_at":"2026-03-16T01:06:09Z","assignee":null,"author_association":"NONE","issue_field_values":[],"type":null,"active_lock_reason":null,"sub_issues_summary":{"total":0,"completed":0,"percent_completed":0},"issue_dependencies_summary":{"blocked_by":0,"total_blocked_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Duplicates\n\n- [x] I have searched the existing issues\n\n### Latest version\n\n- [x] I have tested the latest version\n\n### Current behavior 😯\n\nOn the current `alpha` dist-tag (`@solidjs/start@2.0.0-alpha.2`), my app intermittently throws a hydration mismatch on initial load after the first downward scroll:\n\n```text\nError: Hydration Mismatch. Unable to find DOM nodes for hydration key: ...\n<svg></svg>\n```\n\nThe stack in the original app pointed at the icon render path, and tracing the hydration key back through the component tree narrowed it to the mobile-menu `ChevronDown` SVG rendered inside a Kobalte `CollapsibleTrigger`.\n\nI stripped the app down to a focused repro that keeps only:\n\n- a sticky shell\n- a `@kobalte/core` collapsible trigger\n- a `lucide-solid` `ChevronDown` icon inside that trigger\n- enough page height that the first user action is a vertical scroll\n\nRepro repo: https://github.com/pRizz/solid-start-alpha-kobalte-hydration-repro\n\nImportant context: after migrating the real app to the latest stable line (`@solidjs/start@1.3.2`), the same shell no longer reproduced the hydration issue in my follow-up checks. So this report may be specific to the current alpha dist-tag rather than the stable release.\n\n### Expected behavior 🤔\n\nThe shell should hydrate cleanly, and the first scroll after page load should not emit a hydration-key mismatch for the trigger icon.\n\n### Steps to reproduce 🕹\n\nSteps:\n\n1. `git clone https://github.com/pRizz/solid-start-alpha-kobalte-hydration-repro.git`\n2. `cd solid-start-alpha-kobalte-hydration-repro`\n3. `bun install`\n4. `bun run dev`\n5. Open the local URL in Chrome with a narrow/mobile-width viewport\n6. Refresh the page\n7. Scroll downward before interacting with the menu\n8. Watch the browser console for hydration errors tied to the trigger icon\n\nNotes:\n\n- In the original app, the failing key resolved to the mobile-menu chevron in the shell rather than the page-body content.\n- I could reproduce this in a normal Chrome session while the app was still on `2.0.0-alpha.2`.\n- I was **not** able to reproduce it in a clean headless Playwright session after moving the real app to stable, which is why I am explicitly scoping this report to the current alpha dist-tag and attaching the stripped repo.\n\n### Context 🔦\n\nThis showed up while debugging a separate console failure from the dev overlay. The hydration mismatch itself looks like the primary bug: the overlay problem was secondary noise.\n\nI am filing this because `2.0.0-alpha.2` is still the current `alpha` dist-tag on npm, and the failure narrowed to a very small, common UI shape: a collapsible trigger with an icon in a sticky shell.\n\n### Your environment 🌎\n\n```shell\nSystem:\n  OS: macOS 26.3\n  CPU: arm64\nBinaries:\n  Node: v24.13.0\n  Bun: 1.3.9\nBrowser:\n  Chrome: 146.0.7680.80\nnpmPackages:\n  @solidjs/start: 2.0.0-alpha.2\n  @solidjs/vite-plugin-nitro-2: 0.1.0\n  @solidjs/router: 0.15.4\n  @kobalte/core: 0.13.11\n  lucide-solid: 0.577.0\n  solid-js: 1.9.11\n  vite: 7.3.1\n```\n","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid-start/issues/2108/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid-start/issues/2108/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":"completed","pinned_comment":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid-start/issues/2107","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid-start","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/solidjs/solid-start/issues/2107/labels{/n